job_description:
About UsTory Burch is an American lifestyle brand that embodies the personal style and sensibility of its founder, Chairman, CEO and Chief Creative Officer, Tory Burch. The collection, known for color, print and eclectic details, includes ready-to-wear, shoes, handbags, accessories, home and beauty. Art, music, travel, interiors and the designers own stylish parents are inspirations for the collection.

Our company launched in February 2004 with a single boutique on what was then a remote street in downtown Manhattan. Today, we are a global brand with a presence in more than 50 countries, but in many ways we are only just beginning. There is so much we want to do!

Brand integrity, global inspiration and beautiful products are integral to who we are as a company and what we have accomplished to date. Our incredible team is an equally important part of the equation. We believe that each of our employees play a vital role in our continuing efforts to grow and evolve.

Overview
The Assistant Master Data Analyst will maintain master data objects assigned to them, including responding to requests. This function will encompass all finance master data objects including General Ledger Accounts, Cost Centers, Profit Centers, Vendor Master, Banking Master, Fixed Asset Master, etc.

Responsibilities
Accurate and timely creation and maintenance of master data according to defined processes.
Review requests for completeness and respond to accordingly.
Data entry and or upload master data changes into SAP.
Provide status updates to requests as required.
Adhere to control framework and internal controls.
Review the use of the master data objects and understand how they are being used.
Cross-train with the other member of the master data team to assure adequate backup for all areas.
Conduct special projects as required.

Qualifications
Experience with ERP SAP preferred;
Basic knowledge of accounting principles;
Advanced proficiency is use of MS Office (Excel, PowerPoint, Word, Outlook).
Bachelors degree in Accounting, Finance, Business, etc.;
Minimum of 1-3 years of general master data experience.

DESIRED ATTRIBUTES
Ability to work collaboratively with all departments;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to interface comfortably at all levels both internally and externally;
Able to establish a high level of trust and credibility in the organization;
Attention to detail;
Ability to nurture and work in fast paced, team oriented environment; strong emphasis on team building through training, coaching and mentoring;
Flexible; ability to adapt to changing priorities and multiple tasks;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills.

Responsibilities:

Support Local Medical Affairs Leads on client service teams (2-3 prioritized clients) to grow our presence and relationships in Medical Affairs. Work closely with ZS client teams to lead client business development and client relationship development across our key client accounts;
Provide Medical Affairs consultation beyond 2-3 prioritized clients to support opportunistic growth across Medical Affairs clients for ZS (60+ clients);
Work with technology, operations, strategy, and data science teams at ZS and our clients to develop solutions that advance our clients’ Medical Affairs capabilities;
Stay abreast of current business and industry trends relevant to our clients. Develop a strong point-of-view and establish ZS thought leadership in Medical Affairs, especially as it relates to bridging medical and commercial appropriately;
Market our Medical Affairs service line to increase awareness of ZS capabilities in Med Affairs, build knowledge of our point-of-view, and inform our clients’ perception of the ZS value proposition in Medical Affairs;
Consistently deliver quality client services and drive high-quality work products within expected timeframes and on budget;
Monitor progress, manage risk and ensure key stakeholders are kept informed about progress and expected outcomes;
Effectively lead and motivate teams with diverse skills and backgrounds;
Provide constructive on-the-job feedback/coaching to team members. Foster an innovative and inclusive team-oriented work environment;
Play an active role in counseling and mentoring junior team members within ZS. Work collaboratively and well with cross-office and offshore team members;
Possess in-depth business acumen. Run a growing and profitable Medical Affairs business on the East Coast in the U.S. for ZS, deliver profitable projects, and invest in innovation that supports our growth.
Qualifications:

A Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Life Sciences, Business or related field;
MBA or advanced degree such as MD, PharmD, Or MPH highly preferred;
7-9+ years of experience in the life science industry;
4+ years of management consulting experience;
Demonstrated experience working with Medical Affairs clients;
Demonstrated experience driving revenue within existing clients and in developing new prospects;
Demonstrate ability to quickly assimilate new knowledge;
Executive level presence and communication skills.
A willingness to travel internationally to meet client needs.

Note: To apply for this job, submit your application by clicking on the Apply Now button on this page
